---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Privacy policy — appelsin"
	description="What personal data appelsin processes, why, and your rights."
>
	<div class="flex min-h-screen flex-col">
		<header class="flex items-start justify-between px-8 pt-6 sm:px-12 sm:pt-8">
			<a href="/" aria-label="appelsin.io home" class="block">
				<img src="/logo.svg" alt="appelsin.io" width="110" height="110" />
			</a>
			<nav class="flex items-center gap-3 pt-4 text-sm sm:text-base">
				<a href="/login" class="text-zinc-100 hover:text-orange-400">Login</a>
				<span class="text-zinc-400">|</span>
				<a href="/terms" class="text-zinc-100 hover:text-orange-400">Terms</a>
				<span class="text-zinc-400">|</span>
				<a href="/privacy" class="text-orange-400">Privacy</a>
			</nav>
		</header>

		<main class="mx-auto w-full max-w-3xl px-6 pb-24 pt-8 sm:px-12">
			<h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold text-white sm:text-4xl">
				Privacy policy
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-2 text-sm text-zinc-400">Last updated: 18 May 2026</p>

			<p class="mt-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				This page explains what personal data <strong>appelsin.io</strong>
				processes, why, and what your rights are. We follow the EU General
				Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">1. Who we are</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				appelsin.io is operated by [Legal entity name], CVR [number],
				[address], Denmark. Contact:
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="mailto:hello@appelsin.io">hello@appelsin.io</a>.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				2. What data we process
			</h2>

			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<strong>Hosts</strong> (people paying for an event):
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>email address (account, magic-link login, receipts);</li>
				<li>Stripe customer ID and payment status — we never see card numbers;</li>
				<li>a session token in a first-party cookie;</li>
				<li>event metadata you enter (event name, date, retention setting).</li>
			</ul>

			<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<strong>Guests</strong> (people uploading photos at an event):
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>the photo you upload, plus an optional caption;</li>
				<li>
					a salted fingerprint derived from your IP address and browser, used
					only for rate-limiting and abuse blocking on a single event — it
					cannot identify you across events;
				</li>
				<li>
					the IP address of your upload request, kept in transient access
					logs for up to 30 days.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<p class="mt-4 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<strong>Display viewers</strong> (the big screen at the venue):
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>
					only the event short code; no personal data is sent from the
					display browser beyond standard request logs.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				3. Why we process it (legal bases)
			</h2>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>
					<strong>Contract</strong> with hosts: account, billing, delivering
					the service.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Legitimate interest</strong> with guests: rate-limiting and
					abuse prevention. You can object at any time by contacting us.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Consent</strong> for the photo itself: the host is
					responsible for collecting consent at the venue (see Terms §3).
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				4. Who we share data with
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We use the following sub-processors. We do not sell personal data
				and we do not use it for advertising.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-4 overflow-x-auto">
				<table class="w-full border-collapse text-sm">
					<thead>
						<tr class="border-b border-white/20 text-left text-zinc-100">
							<th class="py-2 pr-4">Vendor</th>
							<th class="py-2 pr-4">Purpose</th>
							<th class="py-2">Location</th>
						</tr>
					</thead>
					<tbody class="text-zinc-200">
						<tr class="border-b border-white/10">
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">Cloudflare</td>
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">
								Hosting, image storage and delivery, realtime
							</td>
							<td class="py-2">EU region for storage; CDN is global</td>
						</tr>
						<tr class="border-b border-white/10">
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">Stripe</td>
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">Payments</td>
							<td class="py-2">EU + US (SCCs in place)</td>
						</tr>
						<tr>
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">Resend</td>
							<td class="py-2 pr-4">Transactional email</td>
							<td class="py-2">EU + US (SCCs in place)</td>
						</tr>
					</tbody>
				</table>
			</div>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				5. Where data is stored
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Primary storage (database, photo bucket) is in Cloudflare’s EU
				region. Edge caching may temporarily serve image variants from a CDN
				node closer to the viewer.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
				6. How long we keep it
			</h2>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>
					<strong>Photos and event metadata</strong>: deleted automatically
					when the retention period of the host’s plan expires (7, 30 or 90
					days after the event end).
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Host account</strong>: deleted on request or 12 months
					after the last login.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Payment records</strong>: 5 years, as required by Danish
					bookkeeping law.
				</li>
				<li><strong>Access logs</strong>: up to 30 days.</li>
			</ul>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">7. Your rights</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Under GDPR you can ask us to:
			</p>
			<ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<li>access the personal data we hold about you;</li>
				<li>correct inaccurate data;</li>
				<li>delete your data (“right to be forgotten”);</li>
				<li>export your data in a portable format;</li>
				<li>restrict or object to processing.</li>
			</ul>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Send any request to
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="mailto:hello@appelsin.io">hello@appelsin.io</a>.
				We aim to respond within 30 days. If you are not satisfied, you can
				complain to the Danish Data Protection Authority (Datatilsynet,
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="https://www.datatilsynet.dk" rel="noopener">datatilsynet.dk</a>).
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">8. Cookies</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We set one first-party cookie for the host login session. No
				analytics or advertising cookies.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">9. Children</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				The service is not intended for users under 16. If you become aware
				that a child has uploaded a photo of themselves, contact us and we
				will delete it.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">10. Security</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				Photos travel directly from the guest’s phone to Cloudflare Images
				over TLS. Database and object storage are encrypted at rest.
				Magic-link login tokens expire after a short window. If we discover
				a personal-data breach affecting you, we will notify you and the
				supervisory authority without undue delay, and at the latest within
				72 hours where required.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">11. Changes</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				We may update this policy. Material changes will be announced by
				email to active hosts at least 14 days before they take effect.
			</p>

			<h2 class="mt-10 text-xl font-semibold text-white">12. Contact</h2>
			<p class="mt-3 leading-relaxed text-zinc-200">
				<a class="text-orange-400 underline hover:text-orange-300" href="mailto:hello@appelsin.io">hello@appelsin.io</a><br />
				[Legal entity name], CVR [number]<br />
				[Postal address], Denmark
			</p>
		</main>
	</div>
</Layout>
